    "description": "An exciting career opportunity awaits you at Bajaj Allianz Life South Asia Partners. We are on the lookout for a dedicated Risk Analyst to strengthen our Ghaziabad-based team.\n\nAbout Bajaj Allianz Life South Asia Partners:\nBajaj Allianz Life South Asia Partners is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Prepare MIS reports for senior management review\n• Ensure compliance with tax regulations and statutory requirements\n• Liaise with banks, regulators, and financial institutions\n• Monitor market trends and provide investment recommendations\n• Monitor financial performance against targets and provide variance analysis\n• Prepare annual reports and investor presentations\n• Coordinate with external auditors during annual audits\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Tech / B.E. in Computer Science or related discipline\n• 3-6 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Bloomberg Terminal\n• Proficiency in Due Diligence\n• Proficiency in Python for Finance\n• Proficiency in Financial Reporting\n• Proficiency in VBA\n• Proficiency in Financial Modeling\n• Proficiency in Power BI\n• Proficiency in SAP FICO\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Company-sponsored certifications\n• Mobile and internet reimbursement\n• Meal coupons and food allowance\n• Life and accident insurance\n• Maternity and paternity leave\n• Salary Range: 7 LPA - 15 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Ghaziabad, Uttar Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Bajaj Allianz Life South Asia Partners!",
